## Example 1 — Transform One Side

Prove that:

`x^3 - y^3 = (x - y)(x^2 + xy + y^2)`

Start with the right side:

`(x - y)(x^2 + xy + y^2)`

Distribute:

`= x(x^2) + x(xy) + x(y^2) - y(x^2) - y(xy) - y(y^2)`

Simplify:

`= x^3 + x^2y + xy^2 - x^2y - xy^2 - y^3`

Combine like terms:

`= x^3 - y^3`

So the right side simplifies to the left side, which proves the identity.

